  sodium: 5 g
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Wash the @sweet potato{2} then chop lengthways into wedges the thickness of your index finger. Toss in a splash of @olive oil{1%splash} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}, then spread in a single layer on a #baking tray{}. Cook on the top shelf of your oven until crispy (~{25%minutes}).

> Save the garlic salt for your burgers!

In a #bowl{} mix together the @British beef mince{500%g}, the @garlic salt{1/2%tsp}, half the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}, the @dried oregano{1.5%tsp} and a few grinds of @black pepper{a few grinds}.

Divide your beef mixture into equal portions, one per person, and then, with your hands, form into burger patties roughly 1 1/2cm thick. Slice the @smoked cheese{80%g} into rounds.

Once your sweet potato is almost ready, split each @brioche bun{4} in half. Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and toast each bun for ~{2%mins} on each side then remove.

> You could use your toaster but whatever happens don't let them burn!

In the same frying pan, heat a splash of @olive oil{1%splash} on medium-high heat. Once hot, gently add in your burger patties and cook for ~{5-6%mins} on each side, or until the meat is fully cooked with no pink bits remaining. Whilst you are cooking the second side, lay your smoked cheese on top (of the cooked side!) for the last minute so that it melts.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @vine tomatoes{4}. Toss the @wild rocket{2%bunch} in a little drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} with a small pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Spread a little of your remaining ketchup on your toasted bun. Place your burger on top, then lay your tomato slices and rocket on top and serve with your sweet potato wedges on the side.

> You can serve any remaining tomatoes and rocket on the side too.